%global pkg_name storablevector

%bcond_with tests

Name:           %{pkg_name}
Version:        0.2.12.1
Release:        0
Summary:        Fast, packed, strict storable arrays with a list interface like ByteString
Group:          Development/Libraries/Haskell

License:        BSD-3-Clause
Url:            https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}
Source0:        https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}-%{version}/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  ghc-Cabal-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-rpm-macros
BuildRequires:  ghc-QuickCheck-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-deepseq-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-non-negative-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-syb-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-transformers-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-unsafe-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-utility-ht-devel
%if %{with tests}
BuildRequires:  ghc-bytestring-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-random-devel
%endif

%description
Fast, packed, strict storable arrays with a list interface, a chunky lazy list
interface with variable chunk size and an interface for write access via the
'ST' monad. This is much like 'bytestring' and 'binary' but can be used for
every 'Foreign.Storable.Storable' type. See also package
<http://hackage.haskell.org/package/vector> with a similar intention.

We do not provide advanced fusion optimization, since especially for lazy
vectors this would either be incorrect or not applicable. However we provide
fusion with lazy lists in the package
<http://hackage.haskell.org/package/storablevector-streamfusion>.


